This paper discusses the use of big data analytics, machine learning, and artificial intelligence in the context of next-generation wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the role of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. Additionally, the paper presents optimization schemes, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and benefits of adopting these technologies, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
